		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Interesting. It's a very good test ROM for showing the bug in the S-PPU that drops the frontmost sprites when the 34-tile overdraw limit is exceeded, not the rearmost sprites like on other sprite-based VDPs.<br /><br />How long does your rotation routine take for a given area of sprite? Or is precomputing that why it white-screened for so long while starting? I'm trying to see how feasible it would have been to make <em>Yoshi's Island</em> without a GSU.

		

